Privacy Policy for ARIS 360

At ARIS 360, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application. Please read this policy carefully. If you do not agree with the terms of this policy, please do not use the application.

1. Information We Collect:
- Personal Information: When you sign up, we collect your name and email address.
- Location Data: We collect location information if you search for nearby properties. (Optional)

2. How We Use Your Information:
- To provide access to the real estate properties listed within the app.
- To allow you to search for properties by name, city, or other details.
- To display properties on a map and show nearby properties if location access is granted.
- To manage your account, including allowing you to change your password, edit your name, or delete your account.
- To enable notifications if you allow them.

3. Guest Access:
- You can use the app as a guest without providing personal information. However, certain features, such as contacting the admin managing sales, will require you to sign up.

4. Security:
- You can set a biometric lock for additional security.
- We take reasonable steps to protect your information but cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Data Retention:
- We will retain your personal data for as long as you have an account. You can delete your account at any time via the app settings.

6. Third-Party Access:
- We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to outside parties.

7. Your Rights:
- You can update your name, change your password, or delete your account at any time through the settings section of the app.

8. Changes to This Policy:
- We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted within the app.

By using ARIS360, you consent to this Privacy Policy.

For further information, please contact us at support@aris360.com or visit our website at aris360.com.
